# Max (Gravity Claw) — Feature Walkthrough

We successfully transformed Max from a basic skeleton into a fully capable, persistent, and intelligent Chief of Staff for Telegram group chats. 

Here are the major upgrades that are now live:

### 1. 🧠 True Memory & Persistence (SQLite)
Previously, making changes to Max's code would restart the bot and wipe his memory. Now, every message is saved to [gravity_claw.db](file:///Users/tahmidnur/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/theresidentialaddress/agents/gravity-claw/gravity_claw.db) (SQLite). Even if the server reboots, Max remembers exactly what you were talking about 5 minutes ago.

### 2. 🌍 Live Website Awareness
Max now has the exact structure of `theresidentialaddress.com` "baked" into his brain. When you ask him to change something, he no longer wastes 10 minutes scanning directories. He goes straight to the exact file. Furthermore, when he makes an edit, he provides you with the live URL link so you can preview it immediately.

### 3. 🚀 Native Deployment Tool
Max now has a `deploy_website` tool. If you say *"Max, push those changes live"*, he will automatically:
- Run `git add .`
- Run `git commit -m "auto-generated description of changes"`
- Run `git push`
This triggers your Vercel deployment instantly, straight from a Telegram chat.

### 4. 📸 Multimodal Vision (Code & Screenshots)
Max can now "see" images natively. If you screenshot a messy padding alignment on the website and send it to the Telegram group saying *"Max, fix this header padding"*, he downloads the highest quality version of the image securely from Telegram, processes it using Google Gemini 2.5 Flash, and edits the code to fix the visual bug.

### 5. 💬 Sticky Conversation (Focus Mode)
Instead of forcing you to tag `@TRAMaxBot` on every message:
- **Engage**: Say *"Max, let's update the pricing table."* to lock his focus.
- **Maintain**: You can reply *"Looks good, also update the Bank page"* and he will natively continue answering without being tagged.
- **Disengage**: If you pivot and say *"Aman, what do you think?"*, Max instantly disengages and stops replying so he doesn't clutter your human conversations.

### 6. ⏳ Real-Time Action Feedback
When Max is performing complex, multi-step code edits across multiple files, he no longer stays silent for 30 seconds. He will send real-time updates directly into the Telegram chat:
- 📖 *Reading files...*
- ✏️ *Editing files...*
- 🚀 *Deploying updates...*
